        "title": "Just a clarification of this code",
        "body": "<p>I just want a short clarification on these two lines of code. What's the difference between these two?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>SuperClass c = new JustTesting(1, 'b');\nJustTesting b = new JustTesting(2, 'c'); \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>By the way, in case you'd want to see the full code, here it is:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>import static java.lang.System.out;\n\npublic class JustTesting extends SuperClass{\n\npublic JustTesting(int firstVar, char secondVar) {\n    super(firstVar, secondVar);\n}\n\npublic static void main(String[] args) {\n    SuperClass c = new JustTesting(1, 'b');\n    JustTesting b = new JustTesting(2, 'c'); \n    out.println(c.firstVar);\n    out.println(b.firstVar);\n}\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
